This structure is derived from T. cruzi parasite surface molecules as a trypomastigote stage-specific epitope, Ssp-3, generated by the parasite transialidase, where the sialic acid is probably linked to beta-D-Gal by a 2-3 linkage. The exact nature of the entire Ssp-3 epitope is unknown, as is the antigen that expresses it, but it is not sialyl-a(2-3)N-acetyllactosamine, since mammal glycoproteins and glycolipids containing that structure are not reactive with epitope-specific mAbs.
